#MEM id=systematic-debugging source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/quinn/skills/superpowers/systematic-debugging/defense-in-depth.md savings=6%
M|Over|tx|When you fix a bug caused by invalid data, adding validation at one place feels sufficient. But that single check can be bypassed by different code paths, refactoring, or mocks.
M|Over|**Co|** Validate at EVERY layer data passes through. Make the bug structurally impossible.
M|Why |Sing|"We fixed the bug"
M|Why |Mult|"We made the bug impossible"
M|Why |Diff|
M|Why |it|Entry validation catches most bugs
M|Why |it|Business logic catches edge cases
M|Why |it|Environment guards prevent context-specific dangers
M|Why |it|Debug logging helps when other layers fail
M|Laye|**Pu|** Reject obviously invalid input at ap boundary
